{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17590612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17590612"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:50:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:50:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15210"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15210","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15210"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.07,0.57,0.32,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7901"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66592"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7901","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7901"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15210"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52045"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"20"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1115"},{"type":"tags","id":"2545"},{"type":"tags","id":"3833"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8741"},{"type":"tags","id":"9419"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19253"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19257"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21319"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66592","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66592"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a rapidly growing lesion on his left ear that has been present for three months (Image). He works as a farmer and has extensive sun exposure. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. The lesion is fixed to underlying cartilage. There is a firm, mobile 3 cm lymph node in the left anterior cervical chain.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the stage of this disease?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stage I","Stage II","Stage III","Stage IVA","Stage IVB"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThere is a 3 cm ulcerated, indurated lesion on the left pinna with rolled edges. This patient presents with what is almost certainly a squamous cell carcinoma (SCC) with features indicating \u003Cstrong\u003EStage III\u003C/strong\u003E disease. The key findings supporting this staging are the presence of a single regional lymph node metastasis and the invasion into the cartilage of the ear. Stage III SCC is defined by either the presence of a single lymph node \u22643 cm in diameter on the same side as the primary tumour, or by deep invasion (beyond subcutaneous fat or \u0026gt;6 mm depth).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage I\u003C/strong\u003E SCCs are confined to the dermis, measure less than 2 cm in greatest dimension, and have fewer than two high-risk features. This patient\u0027s tumour exceeds these criteria in size and invasion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage II\u003C/strong\u003E SCCs are either larger than 2 cm in diameter or have two or more high-risk features but do not have nodal involvement or deep invasion. While this tumour is larger than 2 cm, the presence of nodal disease excludes Stage II.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage IVA\u003C/strong\u003E disease involves multiple lymph nodes or a single node larger than 3 cm, which is not present in this case where there is only a single 3 cm node.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage IVB\u003C/strong\u003E involves distant metastatic disease, which has not been identified in this patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHigh-risk features of SCC include location on the ear (as in this case), lip, or other high-risk areas; poorly defined borders; recurrent lesions; immunosuppression; perineural invasion; and poor differentiation. The presence of these features influences prognosis and treatment decisions but does not alone determine staging.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Squamous cell carcinoma staging depends on tumour size, depth of invasion, and presence of high-risk features.","Stage III squamous cell carcinoma involves either lymph node metastasis or deep invasion.","High-risk features include perineural invasion, poor differentiation, and location on high-risk areas like lips or ears."],"references":["Wang Y, Mukkamalla SKR, Singh R, Babiker HM, Lyons S. Esophageal Cancer. 2024 Aug 17. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29083661","Codipilly DC, Wang KK. Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Esophagus. Gastroenterol Clin North Am. 2022 Sep;51(3):457-484. doi: 10.1016/j.gtc.2022.06.005. Epub 2022 Aug 29. PMID: 36153105","Hadian Y, Howell JY, Ramsey ML, et al. Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma. [Updated 2024 Jul 2]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK441939/","Burton KA, Ashack KA, Khachemoune A. Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma: A Review of High-Risk and Metastatic Disease. Am J Clin Dermatol. 2016 Oct;17(5):491-508. doi: 10.1007/s40257-016-0207-3. PMID: 27358187","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52045"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15210"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21270"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21270"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/tktFUf0qAIAAGoBaEWn2ZG3Xay4htj.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/tktFUf0qAIAAGoBaEWn2ZG3Xay4htj.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":404,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52045","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52045"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T12:29:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T12:30:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7901"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66592"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"20","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/20"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4c","name":"Plastic Surgery","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"h